#Block inheritance 

Start the Active Directory Users and Computer snap-in (Start - Programs - Administrative Tools - 
Active Directory Users and Computers) > Right click on the container  to stop inheriting 
settings from its parent and select Properties > Select the 'Group Policy' tab > Check the 
Block Policy inheritance option > Click Apply then OK

#Link order

Open the Group Policy Management console > In the navigation pane, expand Forest: ForestName, 
expand Domains, and then expand DomainName > Right-click DomainName, and then click Link an 
Existing GPO > In the Select GPO dialog box, select the GPO that want to deploy, and then click OK
> The GPO appears in the Linked Group Policy Objects tab > Select a GPO and click the up or
down arrows to move it.

